reviews.review_text: Just read some recent reviews and seems like they heard some of the complaints? When I was there, they asked for each customers names for the order, they were friendly ish, and the food was made fresh the way it suppose to be.  I ordered a Canadian breakfast special and it took a bit of time to get it.  My take was they were making it , not just having eggs, bacon , sausage, toast sitting around and then slapping it together like at McDonald s. Good experience today .

Very nice & friendly staff I placed an order 30 minutes before their closing time but an extremely nice lady who got my order her name was Harkiran with beautiful smile did not rush me or making me uncomfortable Thank you Harkiran
reviews.response_from_owner_text: It s great to hear you had such a great service! Thanks for taking the time to leave a review.

reviews.review_text: Very nice workers and good Buddy Burgers only one thing can make them even better..smaller onions in the shape of rings...nice thin ones and not cooked so much. Dietary restrictions: Maybe a whole wheat or spelt Bun for the burgers ?
Amazing customer service. I showed up 10 minutes after closing time and the girl working there (Jasmine) didnt hesitate for a second and took my order. She was extremely pleasant and courteous.
This exquisite restaurant fit for gods has created the perfect meal and best meal I have ever had as breakfast, lunch and dinner, the double chubby chicken combo with sprite. 11/10 combo

Those used to the American A&W chain will definitely be blown away by the Canadian ones (theyre operated by different companies). As far as fast food goes here, A&W is usually the tastiest option albeit not the cheapest. You really cant beat caramelized onions on your burgers though.

Dazed & Confused meets underwater turtle herding. Went here at 9AM on a Saturday, positives were there were only 2 other people waiting, and premises appeared bright and clean. The single staff member helping us appeared bewildered with the crush of people waiting, moving so slowly I was wondering if they were in need of assistance.  The lady waiting for her meal had to ask for it to be served to her and reminded twice she also had a coffee.  Maybe the staff person hadnt woken up yet. Asked for parking to be validated.and found out when I went to the kiosk that it hadnt been.  Not impressed with my experience.
Staff have trouble managing lunch rushes (2/3 orders took 15+ minutes & I only order a burger). Poor customer service skills. No apology for late food or if theyre out of stock.
It gets two stars because the other A&W on Cambie & Broadway got 1 star...its bad but not as bad as that one.
AW should take over this location.
Its okay

So I ordered kids chicken stripe, was ask if I wanted juice or milk and I said no, after paying, I realize I should get.jucie for my kids because he needs some liquid to drink after, I ask you know what how much is it for the a kids  juice and the guy that I deal with was preparing my order heard that I want juice, he keeps on saying but he doesnt want it. Anyways, to  make a story short, why did I pay for the juice when it should have come with the kids meal... huh ,

Im an A&W fan, however this A&W is continually dissapointing. Usually fast food chains are highly standardized across locations. This is not the case in this location. Service and food are both always cold. I find out odd that theres just one A&W location that just puts out really poor food and service.

Ordered a sausage and egger with croissant and an apple juice. The lady behind me ordered a sausage and egger with English muffin. When the order came up, I came to grab my order and the lady behind me grabbed it too and claimed she ordered the same thing and was rude about it too. The employee did not even clarify or helped tell her that it was our order. I just gave it to this obnoxious lady and waited. And obviously the next order came up for the sausage and egger with English muffin which no one came to claim since it was that lady s!!! I ended up waiting for 20 mins and the employee gave me orange juice instead of apple juice. When I told her, she s like  it s not orange?    need better customer service and have a number or name system to claim orders or something. Especially with the long line up they have and the potential for people to have the same orders, etc. This was around 10:00am June 2nd.
ordered Teen burger with A&W root beer for $6.99 with coupon. instead root beer i requested oranage juice. why pay the full price for oranage juice. very unsafisfied service with supervisor.  thanks.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for letting us know about your experience. Wed like to look into this. Please send us an email with this information at guestrelations@aw.ca.

reviews.review_text: How could u accept delivery orders while you can not provide parking????? We re getting $50 ticket for picking up the orders for skip and uber or we have to pay $4 everytime for $6 order which is not fair. If you can t provide so do not accept orders

Super stupid that they charge a cup fee when you buy a drink.  What choice do you have if you order a drink?  What s the purpose?  Why don t they just charge more for the drink rather than adding extra fees.  Seems like a rip off.

Worst A&W outlet Ive been to.  I stopped in for a quick breakfast combo prior to an appointment.  The place wasnt busy at all, but I spend 15 min waiting for my food after paying, as other customers came and went.  When I asked about it the cashier acted as if she had no idea what I was talking about, despite me standing there as the only person waiting the entire time.  When I asked for a refund she acted as if she had idea how to do that.  I had to run to my appointment  so just left with no food and no refund.  Not a biggie but...how do they stay in business?

Waited in line 12 minutes starting with only 2 people in front of me. First they told me they wouldn t accept my coupon which then ended up accepting then they gave me my burger with onions when I asked for no onions and it came with a half full root beer when I asked for Diet Coke.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for taking the time to write about your experience, Jake. Wed like to look into this. Please send us an email with this feedback at guestrelations@aw.ca so we can follow up.

Poor customer service skills, everyone that works here seems like they hate their job. Today I asked for ketchup, the lady glared at me and passed me one ketchup packet, I asked if I could have more and she glared again, passed me one more packet of ketchup and walked away rolling her eyes. Incredibly rude and out of no where.

Horrible experience.. waited 30 minutes from ordering to receiving my food... customers infront had their orders given to them wrong.... missing items etc.. hire more staff if the current ones arent able to work efficient enough... Nov 3rd from 43:0-5:00PM
